INSERT IGNORE INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES (41630, 0, 0, 'Skipping happily into the first one, I failed to notice that there are more than one bad guy around. In fact, there are about a half dozen of the lovely little buggers who aren\'t right near any of the needles but just waiting around for the call. Hey team - noobs attacking! So you\'ll get to meet lots of new friends at each needle. Just be prepared to deal with multiple mobs and they have one fun trait - you can\'t run out of combat. They will pursue you across Coldarra and to the ends of the earth. I saw one in London two weeks later but maybe he was just picking up his new shirts.', 0);
INSERT IGNORE INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES (41631, 0, 0, 'For those having trouble and getting killed quickly. I walked into the vault with 830+ and it was dire. I removed everything that could take damage and this dropped me to 368. Lvl 110 Ilvl 368. It was much easier after that. You can still die but the cost is lower and the fights are easier. When you get to the last level re-equip all your stuff as it will help you survive the oh so long 8 seconds. $0.02 Cheers...', 0);
INSERT IGNORE INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES (41770, 0, 0, 'I belief things has changed in here. The things written down here are no longer the case: 1. Kill mobs (they respawn but very very very slowly do don\'t wait for them) 2. Kill the miniboss 3. Take the slidething (as allways you wont fall) 4. Hand in quest and take the portal that is at the quest hand in point back to the Class hall. No need of a heartstone or whatever.', 0);
