INSERT IGNORE INTO `quest_request_items` (`ID`, `EmoteOnComplete`, `EmoteOnIncomplete`, `CompletionText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES (52505, 0, 0, 'Has anyone else noticed the rewards for these quests, obviously are class dependent, but also off spec in most cases? It just dawned on me. I ran a Pandaren Monk through the Darkshore world quests just a few minutes ago. The reward for this quest was Serene Disciple\'s Trident . I did the quest as it was good for my off spec (I rarely use). But my main spec Windwalker, uses fist weapons. Ok, so I wait. Well, I logged off my Monk and onto my Enhancement Shaman, which uses Maces. I look at this quest and what is the reward for my Shaman doing it? Earthpyre Claws ! Not Mace, that I can actually use with my spec, but the exact item I needed for my elemental off spec. Really Blizzard, when you set these reward systems up you didn\'t think to set them for the spec that\'s actually doing the world quest? Am I ever going to see fist weapons for my Monk in these quests while playing my Monk? ... in Windwalker spec that is. I\'ve played it everyday so far and so far other classes have seen the fist weapons, but not the Monk. IDK maybe I need to play it in Mistweaver in order to get the fist weapons I need for Windwalker. How asinine is that? Blizzard\'s programmers can set the rewards up by class but specifying spec is beyond their capabilities? I don\'t think so. Or, as I\'ve posted in numerous posts, is it just one more way the programmers have thought of to screw with the player base? If they have the ability to set the loot table by class, then they HAVE the ability to set it by spec as well. Makes you wonder why they didn\'t, doesn\'t it. var lv_screenshots = [{\"id\":747257,\"user\":\"Rantsi\",\"date\":\"2018-06-25T16:01:52-05:00\",\"width\":3840,\"height\":2160,\"type\":5,\"typeId\":52505,\"imageType\":2,\"staffOnly\":false,\"sticky\":1}]; var lv_videos = []; var g_pageInfo = {\"type\":5,\"typeId\":52505,\"name\":\"Pruning the Thorns\"}; WH.Layout.set({breadcrumb: [0, 3, 1, 148]}); //]]> // Links Pruning the Thorns &nbsp; Auberdine Guardian slain &nbsp;( 8 ) &nbsp; Lieutenant Aylissa Silverarrow slain &nbsp;( 1 ) {\"ox\":\"This quest has objectives in $$.\",\"sx\":\"This quest starts in $$.\",\"ex\":\"This quest ends in $$.\",\"sex\":\"This quest starts and ends in $$.\",\"osx\":\"This quest has objectives and starts in $$.\",\"oex\":\"This quest has objectives and ends in $$.\",\"osx_ey\":\"This quest has objectives and starts in $$ and ends in $$.\",\"oex_sy\":\"This quest has objectives and ends in $$ and starts in $$.\",\"sx_ey\":\"This quest starts in $$ and ends in $$.\",\"ox_sy\":\"This quest starts in $$ and has objectives in $$.\",\"ox_ey\":\"This quest has objectives in $$ and ends in $$.\",\"ox_sey\":\"This quest starts and ends in $$ and has objectives in $$.\",\"ox_sy_ez\":\"This quest starts in $$, has objectives in $$ and ends in $$.\"} // See if you\'ve already completed this by typing: /run print(C_QuestLog.IsQuestFlaggedCompleted(52505)) WH.clickToCopy(document.currentScript.parentNode, \"\\/run print(C_QuestLog.IsQuestFlaggedCompleted(52505))\");', 0);
